  ghostscript-gpl-8.64-r2.ebuild:
  Marking ghostscript-gpl-8.64-r2 ppc64 and ppc for bug 261087

*ghostscript-gpl-8.64-r2 (19 Mar 2009)

  19 Mar 2009; Peter Volkov <pva@gentoo.org>
  +ghostscript-gpl-8.64-r2.ebuild:
  Fixed security issue: integer overflows in ICC library, bug #261087, thank
  Robert Buchholz for report. Finaly respect LDFLAGS, bug #209803.

  08 Mar 2009; Raúl Porcel <armin76@gentoo.org>
  ghostscript-gpl-8.63.ebuild:
  s390/sh stable

  07 Mar 2009; Peter Volkov <pva@gentoo.org> ghostscript-gpl-8.64-r1.ebuild:
  ~mips added, we need to kill ghostscript-esp.

*ghostscript-gpl-8.64-r1 (28 Feb 2009)

  28 Feb 2009; Timo Gurr <tgurr@gentoo.org> +ghostscript-gpl-8.64-r1.ebuild:
  Revbump applying upstream regression fix (bug #259774) and ldflags patches
  which went upstream (bug #215913 and #258313, thanks to Kevin Pyle and
  Hanno Boeck).

*ghostscript-gpl-8.64 (06 Feb 2009)

  06 Feb 2009; Timo Gurr <tgurr@gentoo.org> -ghostscript-gpl-8.61-r1.ebuild,
  +ghostscript-gpl-8.64.ebuild:
  Version bump. Adds support for libpaper. Don't install gsc anymore in
  favor of gambit (bug #253064).

